OBJECTIVE: To investigate the differences in costs and outcomes of Down syndrome 
screening using data from the First and Second Trimester Evaluation of Risk 
(FASTER) Trial.
METHODS: Seven possible screening options for Down syndrome were compared: 1) 
Triple Screen-maternal serum alpha fetoprotein, estriol, and hCG; 2) 
Quad-maternal serum alpha fetoprotein, estriol, hCG, and Inhibin A; 3) Combined 
First-nuchal translucency, pregnancy-associated plasma protein A (PAPP-A), free 
beta-hCG; 4) Integrated-nuchal translucency, PAPP-A, plus Quad; 5) Serum 
Integrated-PAPP-A, plus Quad; 6) Stepwise Sequential-Combined First plus Quad 
with results given after each test; and 7) Contingent Sequential-Combined First 
